<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="subsec-1-1-1" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">

    <p>A <term>proposition</term> is a statement that can take only one of two values: truth or false. Propositions do not have variables.</p>

    <example>
        <p>The following are examples of propositions:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>It is raining.</li>
            <li><m>2+2=4</m></li>
            <li><m>2+5=4</m></li>
            <li>I hate math.</li>
            <li>I love math.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Whereas these are not propositions. Can you tell why?</p>
        <ul>
            <li>She has my phone.</li>
            <li>Stop!</li>
            <li><m>x+2=4</m></li>
            </ul>
    </example>

</section>